snippet: Paul George scored 32 points, including 11 in the final 4½ minutes Friday, to help the Indiana Pacers snap a four-game losing streak with a 111-101 victory over the Chicago Bulls....
lead_paragraph: Paul George scored 32 points, including 11 in the final 4½ minutes Friday, to help the Indiana Pacers snap a four-game losing streak with a 111-101 victory over the Chicago Bulls.

headline.main: George Brings Back Fun for Pacers in 111-101 Win Over Bulls
